### Blockers
 -  None.

##  Outcome
 -  **LANDED `041e4bd5`** (2026-06-16): `JABCutf8Decode` now validates inbound
    UTF-8 via abc's `utf8sValid`/`utf8sDrain32` (rejects overlong forms, lone
    surrogates, truncated multibyte, bad continuation, > U+10FFFF) and decodes
    valid bytes to a UTF-16 JS string; `JABCutf8Encode` trims the trailing NUL
    so the typed-array byteLength is the real UTF-8 byte count (`"hello"`→5).
    The Encode-NUL change was applied (NOT deferred): `test.js`:67 and the
    generated `test.js.c` blob were synced 6→5 in lockstep, and the C++
    harness `ROWS` byteLengths dropped by one — `JABCtest` stays green. C++
    repro rows added to `js/test/jabc_test.cpp` (`run_utf8_decode_repro`):
    red with the stub/incl-NUL code, green after. ASAN/LSan clean (only the
    suppressed JSC-internal singleton leak). All 3 JABC ctests pass.

